        @Nullable
public java.lang.String getSaveFolder()

        Returns:
        The sub-folder name to save this world's chunks to.

      • getMovementFactor

        public double getMovementFactor()
        The dimension's movement factor. Whenever a player or entity changes dimension from world A to world B, their coordinates are multiplied by worldA.provider.getMovementFactor() / worldB.provider.getMovementFactor() Example: Overworld factor is 1, nether factor is 8. Traveling from overworld to nether multiplies coordinates by 1/8.
        Returns:
        The movement factor

      • shouldClientCheckLighting

        public boolean shouldClientCheckLighting()
        If this method returns true, then chunks received by the client will have Chunk.resetRelightChecks() called on them, queuing lighting checks for all air blocks in the chunk (and any adjacent light-emitting blocks). Returning true here is recommended if the chunk generator used also does this for newly generated chunks.
        Returns:
        true if lighting checks should be performed

      • getLightmapColors

        public void getLightmapColors(float partialTicks,
                              float sunBrightness,
                              float skyLight,
                              float blockLight,
                              float[] colors)
        Allows for manipulating the coloring of the lightmap texture. Will be called for each 16*16 combination of sky/block light values.
        Parameters:
        partialTicks - Progress between ticks.
        sunBrightness - Current sun brightness.
        skyLight - Sky light brightness factor.
        blockLight - Block light brightness factor.
        colors - The color values that will be used: [r, g, b].
        See Also:
        EntityRenderer.updateLightmap(float)

                             double rotation)
        Determine if the cursor on the map should 'spin' when rendered, like it does for the player in the nether.
        Parameters:

        x - X Position
        z - Z Position
        rotation - the regular rotation of the marker
        Returns:

      • initCapabilities

        @Nullable
public ICapabilityProvider initCapabilities()
        Called from World.initCapabilities(), to gather capabilities for this world. It's safe to access world here since this is called after world is registered. On server, called directly after mapStorage and world data such as Scoreboard and VillageCollection are initialized. On client, called when world is constructed, just before world load event is called. Note that this method is always called before the world load event.
        Returns:
        initial holder for capabilities on the world

      • getMusicType

        @Nullable
public MusicTicker.MusicType getMusicType()
        Called on the client to get the music type to play when in this world type. At the time of calling, the client player and world are guaranteed to be non-null
        Returns:
        null to use vanilla logic, otherwise a MusicType to play in this world

      • canSleepAt

        public WorldProvider.WorldSleepResult canSleepAt(EntityPlayer player,

        Determines if the player can sleep in this world (or if the bed should explode for example).
        Parameters:
        player - The player that is attempting to sleep
        pos - The location where the player tries to sleep at (the position of the clicked on bed for example)
        Returns:
        the result of a player trying to sleep at the given location

      • getSunBrightnessFactor

        public float getSunBrightnessFactor(float par1)
        The current sun brightness factor for this dimension. 0.0f means no light at all, and 1.0f means maximum sunlight. This will be used for the "calculateSkylightSubtracted" which is for Sky light value calculation.
        Returns:
        The current brightness factor
